est.com/pin/562527809705363049/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:19;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:44:"why does my adjustable chair keep going down";s:4:"slug";s:44:"why-does-my-adjustable-chair-keep-going-down";s:5:"title";s:138:"Walnew High Back Ergonomic Executive Office Chair Pu Leather White Walmart Com White Office Chair Ergonomic Desk Chair Modern Office Chair";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/49/f5/ad/49f5ad332b9a0f6a50cdcb9cf09a9e4d.png";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT6BnCH-pR_Fz2tZ4K7x8sNyQQ2r3f_MVEBVL1qx9IA7DlM3WR6R_0CXWXYv5vWuw7dw00";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:1000;s:6:"height";i:1000;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/110127153376621948/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:44:"why does my adjustable chair keep going down";s:4:"slug";s:44:"why-does-my-adjustable-chair-keep-going-down";s:5:"title";s:65:"Office Chair Won T Stay Up Keeps Sinking 4 Easy Fixes Office Work";s:3:"alt";s:65:"office chair won t stay up keeps sinking 4 easy fixes office work";s:3:"url";s:81:"http://officeandwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Office-Chair-Wont-Stay-Up.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRCvmFuPT260BMNIze4ckxklapkGfp4WFamWQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:429;s:6:"height";i:700;s:6:"source";s:60:"https://officeandwork.com/office-chair-wont-stay-up-sinking/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"officeandwork.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:49:{i:0;s:60:"There is actually a very simple reason for why this happens.";i:1;s:44:"The office chair cylinder has lost its lift.";i:2;s:85:"An office chair cylinder is the part of the chair that connects the base to the seat.";i:3;s:57:"And it is what allows us to adjust the chair up and down.";i:4;s:42:"Inside the chair cylinder is Nitrogen gas.";i:5;s:30:"Every time you sit down on it.";i:6;s:42:"What is going on and why is it doing that.";i:7;s:17:"Its not just you.";i:8;s:64:"This can happen to your chair after a few years of frequent use.";i:9;s:98:"The valve that your seat height lever controls is controlled by a piston that lets air in and out.";i:10;s:104:"When your chair keeps sinking this means that valve also known as a chair cylinder is no longer working.";i:11;s:43:"In order to fix it you will either have to.";i:12;s:154:"Faults in the lift mechanism Sometimes the cause of an office chair not going up or down is a fault in the lift mechanism rather than the cylinder itself.";i:13;s:146:"In this case the problem usually lies with the lever not pressing the button on top of the gas cylinder that allows the chair to move up and down.";i:14;s:199:"Fortunately if you have an issue with adjusting your chairs seat height there is a quick and simple fix when it just stays stuck in the lowest position or will refuse to rise to the highest position.";i:15;s:62:"This fix involves two persons but it can be done solo as well.";i:16;s:61:"Get someone to hold down the base of the chair on the ground.";i:17;s:107:"For real faulty pneumatic spring action also called gas lift heh going on most likely a ball valve failure.";i:18;s:78:"Get a new chair unless its real aspensive then itll be covered under warranty.";i:19;s:104:"When your chair keeps sinking this means that valve also known as a chair cylinder is no longer working.";i:20;s:81:"In order to fix it you will either have to replace the piston or get a new chair.";i:21;s:67:"One may also ask how do you fix an office chair that tilts forward.";i:22;s:73:"Find the tilt adjustment knob for your office chair beneath the seat pan.";i:23;s:88:"The arms are what connect the base to the bottom of the seat so they count here as well.";i:24;s:131:"As we talked about earlier the pneumatic cylinder is what makes your chair height adjustable and is part of the base of your chair.";i:25;s:43:"Spindle attaches the pneumatic cylinder to.";i:26;s:111:"The best thing about using this method to keep your chair up is that it allows you to change the height easily.";i:27;s:96:"If the desired height has not been attained you can add more pieces of slit pipes to achieve it.";i:28;s:110:"Overall having a chair that will not stay up can be annoying and can also negatively affect your productivity.";i:29;s:46:"Its located inside the red circle to the left.";i:30;s:143:"Because the spring is not strong enough to keep you up and there is no seal to trap the air the chair will slowly sink down when you sit in it.";i:31;s:119:"Usually the rest of the office chair is still functional but it becomes unusable if you cant sit at the correct height.";i:32;s:118:"The gas cylinder also referred to as the gas lift or pneumatic cylinder causes some of the most common chair problems.";i:33;s:136:"If you have a gas cylinder that ceases to work correctly youll find that you are slowly sinking while sitting in your home office chair.";i:34;s:59:"Some of the most common reasons for this happening include.";i:35;s:84:"After several years of use your chair will no longer hold the position it is set at.";i:36;s:96:"The lever that normally lets you adjust the height activates a valve in the pneumatic piston on.";i:37;s:209:"When the pneumatic cylinder on your office or computer chair goes kaput as they are wont to do often after just a few years you may find that even the manufacturer doesnt have any suggestions on how to fix it.";i:38;s:88:"Or you might want to buy a new gas cylinder but these are costly and can go bad as well.";i:39;s:117:"Youre in luck -- folks reluctant to consign an otherwise perfectly fine comfortable office chair to the landfill can.";i:40;s:88:"A pneumatic cylinder is attached to the chairs mechanism located under the seat cushion.";i:41;s:87:"This cylinder allows for quick and easy adjustment throughout a specified height range.";i:42;s:157:"This adjustment is often accomplished through the use of a paddle or lever located underneath the seat cushion on either